    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-23T10:41:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-23T10:41:00-05:00" n="454"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d454">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/143</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GJW1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Garrett</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-23T16:00:00+00:19">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 23, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 10 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1920. Your 924, January 19, 12 a.m. I gave assurances as you authorized and have
                    received a written reply dated January 22 as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>The Netherlands Government hereby guarantee that the steamship <hi
                                rend="italic">Nieuw Amsterdam</hi> will immediately return after her
                            next homeward voyage. Signed, The Minister for Foreign Affairs,
                                <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LJJ1">Loudon</persName>.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
